{"title": "Decoy Leader", "content": "The Man Behind the Man controls a real leader behind the scenes. Some leaders may even employ a Body Double to confuse assassins. But sometimes, that leader puts a decoy in front of them to avoid the limelight and long daggers.\n\nA Decoy Leader takes the place of a leader and impersonates them, often conducting him or herself as if they were the real deal. Often, the real leader feeds them instructions via audio device, hand signals, extensive training, or other means so the leader can conduct meaningful policy. Usually, the decoy is willing to die for the leader, and has little to no political ambitions of their own.\n\nWhere this gets interesting is that the decoy doesn't need to look anything like the leader either. The leader may be a Master of Disguise or can at least clean up nicely, which they'll use in order to move around royal and civil society freely. In fact, the leader will likely enjoy going about with the common folk. Of course, a savvy hero or villain will be able to tell this King Incognito out.\n\nCompare Puppet King, where the actual legal leader has become purely a tool for somebody else. The logical extreme of this trope is the El Cid Ploy, where the real leader may be missing or even dead but still \"commands\" because another is impersonating him or (as in the original) no one realizes that he's dead. Also compare with The Man in Front of the Man, for when The Man Behind the Man poses as a supposed minion of the Decoy Leader.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DecoyLeader", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/RakuinNoMonshou", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/FantasticFour", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheJoker", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BatmanBegins", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TotalRecall1990", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Dave", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/StarWars", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ThePhantomMenace", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ANewHope", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheLastKingOfScotland", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SupermanII", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheEagleHasLanded", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/WildWildWest", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/IronMan3", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Gor", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/BattleTechExpandedUniverse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/XWingSeries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/TheHitchhikersGuideToTheGalaxy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TwentyFour", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/ArrestedDevelopment", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StargateSG1", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Utopia", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KamenRiderV3", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/KamenRiderAmazon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/Paranoia", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/HenryVI", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BangaiO", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DarkSouls", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MaxPayne", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/Fallout2", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TheElderScrollsVSkyrim", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/GenocideMan"], "non_media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheManBehindTheMan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BodyDouble", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProfessionalKiller", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasterOfDisguise", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SheCleansUpNicely", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KingIncognito", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PuppetKing", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ElCidPloy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheManInFrontOfTheMan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheManBehindTheMan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GreaterScopeVillain", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SealedEvilInACan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NumberTwo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Comicbook/SteelgripStarkeyAndTheAllPurposePowerTool", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActuallyADoombot", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MacGuffin", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MultipleChoicePast", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Mooks", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KingIncognito", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActionGirl", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KneelBeforeZod", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShaggyDogStory", "/pmwiki